entries.notes: #airing+ some scenes take reflecting to truly appreciate, not guaranteed to happen without watching it airing; also the author commentary/staff diaries enhance the experience, and it's likely that i would only skim it if i binged it; the impatience for more content causing me to read the LNs/rewatch existing episodes bolstered my enjoyment; the extra touches that use the visual medium to further convey distinctions between self-perception and "reality" (as told in the original novel) elevate the story beyond its original form
#airing+ stayed in my thoughts despite the weekly breaks, wondering and hoping enhanced the impact of the mystery/suspense
